# Zeno web (marketing site + waitlist) — environment variables.
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored). Every var here is optional: the app runs
# with sensible defaults / safe fallbacks when unset.

# Where the "backend status" helper (src/api/backend.ts) points — not required
# for the site to function, since nothing user-facing calls the API directly.
# PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787/api/v1

# Waitlist signups (app/api/waitlist/route.ts): posted to this webhook (Slack/
# Zapier/any collector) if set. Required in production — most serverless hosts
# (e.g. Vercel) have a read-only function filesystem, so without a webhook the
# NDJSON file-append fallback throws and the route 502s.
# WAITLIST_WEBHOOK_URL=

# Local/file-based fallback path for waitlist signups when WAITLIST_WEBHOOK_URL
# is unset (only works where the filesystem is writable, e.g. local dev).
# WAITLIST_FILE=.data/waitlist.ndjson

# The /analytics dashboard renders synthetic (seeded, not real) sample data. It
# is hidden in production (404) unless this is set to "1" — e.g. for a demo.
# SHOW_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS=
